##Phishing Attacks

#### Look through Ethan's emails below and see which ones might be legit and which might be phishing attacks.

<div style="font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6;">


  <hr>

  <p><strong>Message A – Text</strong></p>
  <p>
    Hey Ethan — I’m Jess, a student ambassador with UW’s freshman photo club.<br><br>
    We’re putting together a welcome feature for incoming students.<br><br>
    Mind sending your favorite photo and email so we can include you?
  </p>

  <hr>

  <p><strong>Message B – Email</strong></p>
  <p><em>Subject:</em> <strong>Canon R50 – Warranty Registration Incomplete</strong></p>
  <p>
    Hi Ethan,<br><br>
    Thank you for purchasing the Canon R50. Our records indicate your warranty registration is still incomplete.<br><br>
    Register now to ensure full coverage, including protection against accidental damage and theft.<br><br>
    Complete your registration here:<br>
    <a href="#">register.canon-support.com</a><br><br>
    — Canon Product Protection Services
  </p>

  <hr>

  <p><strong>Message C – Instagram DM</strong></p>
  <p>
    <strong>From: @TheVioletLanternsUW</strong><br><br>
    Hey Ethan! I’m with a local indie band playing at UW’s welcome week.<br>
    We’re offering free tickets to new students.<br><br>
    Just need your full name, birthday, and mailing address to get you on the list.<br>
    Spots are filling fast — hit us back soon!
  </p>

</div>


##Breach Reports
#### A data breach is a security incident where sensitive, confidential, or private information is accessed, disclosed, or stolen by unauthorized individuals.

#### Look through Ethan's breach report to try to determine what happened and what type of password attack your user was vulnerable to.

<div style="font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6;">

  <h3 style="color: #00838f;">Breach Report</h3>
  <p><strong>Service Breached:</strong> CloudVault Photo Backup<br>
     <strong>Login Location:</strong> Multiple IPs (rotating, high-frequency script behavior)<br>
     <strong>Time of Access:</strong> 6:20–6:43 p.m.<br>
     <strong>AI Analysis:</strong> Abnormal activity flagged due to high-frequency login attempts from rotating IP addresses.
  </p>

  <p>Over 200 password attempts were recorded prior to access.<br>
     The password used was: <strong>CanonR50</strong><br>
     Attempts were clustered around photography-related keywords and phrases commonly found on the user’s profile.
  </p>

  <p><strong>AI Analysis:</strong> Attempted passwords followed thematic keyword sequence based on user content.<br>
     The attack appeared to use a script simulating human typing speed.<br>
     No files were modified or deleted during the session.<br>
     <strong>AI Analysis:</strong> Account had not backed up any new photos in the past 30 days.
  </p>

  <br>

  <h3 style="color: #00838f;">Password Attacks</h3>

  <table style="width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; border:1px solid #ccc; font-size: 15px;">
    <tr>
      <td style="font-weight:bold; padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">Credential stuffing attack</td>
      <td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">
        When attackers use real usernames and passwords (often from past breaches) to break into other accounts.
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="font-weight:bold; padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">Password guessing attack</td>
      <td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">
        When attackers try different passwords for one account, hoping to guess the right one.
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="font-weight:bold; padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">Password spraying attack</td>
      <td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">
        When an attacker tries one common password on many different accounts to avoid detection.
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="font-weight:bold; padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">Brute force attack</td>
      <td style="padding:10px; border:1px solid #ccc;">
        When an attacker rapidly tries a large number of possible passwords on one account, using automated tools to find the correct one.
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>

</div>

